  "text": "Since polymorphism patterns produced by a selective sweep can be confounded by those resulting from demographic events, e.g., population structure or a recent bottleneck, we applied the GOF test proposed by [CITATION_1] . We obtained L GOF ¼ 467 with a Monte Carlo P-value estimate of 0.81. Therefore, the significant LR KS value is unlikely to be a false positive, i.e., the result of demographic forces alone. This result is supported by the [CITATION_2] test, which also yielded a significantly large likelihood ratio (LR KN ) of the selective sweep vs. the neutral model (LR KN ¼ 17.09, P ¼ 0.05 in comparison to 10,000 simulated neutral data sets).",
